=== Setsusha ===
[[File:Cho Shrine Old Main Hall (Inari Shrine).jpg|thumb|{{center|Inari Shrine}}{{small|The shrine building is the former main hall of Cho Shrine. Repairs were completed in 2017. The roof was changed from copper sheet to persimmon. }}<br />{{small|A cultural property designated by Saitama City. }}]]
* Inari Shrine
*: The shrine building is the former main hall of Chojinja Shrine. The roof is {{jalink|shingled||persimmon shingled}}. According to the ridge tag, it was built in {{jalink|Kyoho|Q1145048}}18 ({{jalink|1733|Q6972}}) and was used as the main shrine until the {{jalink|Ansei|Q1327259}} years ({{jalink|1854|Q7670}}-{{jalink|1860|Q7691}}). There are many carvings of rabbits, reflecting the Tsukimachi belief of Cho Shrine. This shrine building is designated as a cultural property by Saitama City <ref name="Explanation board"/>.
* Chogu Tenjin Shrine
* Konpira Shrine
Several other companies are located within the precincts.
